016package org.lifstools.jmzqc;
017
018import java.util.List;
019import java.util.Objects;
020
021/**
022 * Element containing metadata and qualityMetrics for a single run.
023 *
024 * Base element from which both runQuality and setQuality elements are derived.
025 *
026 * Element containing metadata and qualityMetrics for a collection of related
027 * runs (set).
028 */
029public class BaseQuality {
030
031    private Metadata metadata;
032    private List<QualityMetric> qualityMetrics;// = Collections.emptyList();
033
034    public BaseQuality(){}
035    
036    public BaseQuality(Metadata metadata, List<QualityMetric> qualityMetrics) {
037        this.metadata = metadata;
038        this.qualityMetrics = qualityMetrics;
039    }
040
041    public Metadata getMetadata() {
042        return metadata;
043    }
044
045    public void setMetadata(Metadata metadata) {
046        this.metadata = metadata;
047    }
048
049    public List<QualityMetric> getQualityMetrics() {
050        return qualityMetrics;
051    }
052
053    public void setQualityMetrics(List<QualityMetric> qualityMetrics) {
054        this.qualityMetrics = qualityMetrics;
055    }
056
057    @Override
058    public int hashCode() {
059        int hash = 7;
060        hash = 97 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.metadata);
061        hash = 97 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.qualityMetrics);
062        return hash;
063    }
064
065    @Override
066    public boolean equals(Object obj) {
067        if (this == obj) {
068            return true;
069        }
070        if (obj == null) {
071            return false;
072        }
073        if (getClass() != obj.getClass()) {
074            return false;
075        }
076        final BaseQuality other = (BaseQuality) obj;
077        if (!Objects.equals(this.metadata, other.metadata)) {
078            return false;
079        }
080        return Objects.equals(this.qualityMetrics, other.qualityMetrics);
081    }
082
083}
